  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span>Choose from four hotels with Chia Laguna Resort, ranging from four to five stars and each offering a unique style. Facilities for all rooms include air conditioning, satellite TV, free wifi, minibar, safe and hairdryers.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>HOTEL VILLAGE – 4*</strong></span> (240 rooms)</p>
<p><em>The Hotel Village has a central location in the resort, and the spacious rooms and proximity to the children’s clubs makes it a great choice for families.</em></p>
<p><strong>Classic Cottages</strong> measure 22m² and are set amongst the verdant Mediterranean gardens. Most are on the upper floor and have a window overlooking the village (it’s possible to upgrade to a room with a balcony for a supplement).</p>
<p><strong>Garden Cottages</strong> are set on the ground floor and come with a small, private garden that’s furnished with a table and chairs. They measure 22m².</p>
<p><strong>Superior Cottages</strong> offer a bright, sunny space with large patio doors leading onto a private garden. They have a bit more space at 25m².</p>
<p><strong>Family Classic Cottages</strong> sleep up to four people with two separate bedrooms. Family Garden Cottages and Family Superior Cottages have a mezzanine floor for the second bedroom and private furnished gardens – the Superior cottages also come with a second bathroom. They start from 40m².</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>HOTEL LAGUNA – 5*</strong></span> (74 rooms)</p>
<p><em>Hotel Laguna enjoys sea views from its elevated terraces close to the edge of the resort. It’s a perfect choice for couples, with a more exclusive feel.</em></p>
<p><strong>Superior Rooms</strong> have been finished in pastel colours and enjoy a terrace or balcony with partial sea views.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Rooms</strong> offer plenty of space and captivating sea views from their furnished terrace or garden.<br />Junior Suites offer an open-plan living room and a large terrace with fantastic sea views.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>HOTEL SPAZIO OASI - 5*</strong></span> (34 rooms)</p>
<p><em>This boutique hotel within Chia Laguna Resort boasts newly renovated rooms and excellent outdoor areas looking out over the resort's Mediterranean gardens.</em></p>
<p><strong>Oasi Garden Rooms </strong>are located on the ground floor with elegant furnishings and large windows with garden views. You're just steps away from the hotel's exclusive pool, too.</p>
<p><strong>Oasi Family Rooms </strong>are on the upper floors and have two separate bedrooms, sleeping up to four people.</p>
<p><strong>Oasi Superior Rooms </strong>offer plenty of space and sleep up to four people. They're located on the first floor of the hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Oasi Deluxe Rooms </strong>have a balcony with superb views over the bay of Chia, as well as a lovely sitting area. These rooms are also available with a private garden and separate living room (the garden rooms will not have sea views).</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">HOTEL BAIA - 4*</span> </strong>(77 rooms)</p>
<p><em>The newest hotel at Chia Laguna Resort, Hotel Baia is nestled among the gardens that lead down towards the beach.</em></p>
<p><strong>Presitge Parco Rooms </strong>have been finished in a modern style with light colours and exposed beams.</p>
<p><strong>Prestige Laguna Rooms </strong>enjoy a furnished patio with views over the lagoon, and plenty of space inside with <span>26m².</span></p>
<p><strong>Prestige Mare Rooms</strong> enjoy unforgettable sea views. </p>]]></roomsDescription>
